  <body>
    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>ECUADOR WINS BANANA RULING</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Elizabeth Olson</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Olson, Elizabeth</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>World Trade Organization authorizes Ecuador to impose punitive measures on European Union goods and to withhold copyright protection for sound recordings like compact discs to retaliate for European Union's failure to revise its import policy on bananas; Ecuador sought sanctions after it successfully contested European policy, which favors former colonies primarily in Caribbean, as violating international trading rules; ruling is significant because it represents first time trade body has approved sanctions that invalidates intellectual property protections (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The World Trade Organization authorized Ecuador to impose punitive measures on European Union goods and to withhold copyright protection for sound recordings like compact discs to retaliate for the European Union's failure to revise its import policy on bananas. Ecuador, the world's largest banana exporter, sought the sanctions after it successfully contested the European policy, which favors former colonies primarily in the Caribbean, as violating international trading rules. The W.T.O. ruling was significant because it represents the first time the trade body has approved a sanction that invalidates intellectual property protections.</p>
        <p>Elizabeth Olson</p>
      </block>
